Summary: Add 'change status' to action menu on Scopes page.
Creator: Cathy Sanford
Description:
It appears we just copied what was in classic for view, but we added an edit modal, and you can't edit status there. In Equipment we put Change Status on the Action Menu, and navigate to the classic page INV>Equip>Change Status. We need to do the same thing in Scopes. 

This is a worthy request, but we should tackle this when we migrate instruments. This is because they share much of the same code. We should create a service that updates statuses not only for scopes but also instruments. Perhaps the update process for scopes actually calls an 'InstrumentService' method that updates status for both entities. 

Censitrac.Domain.Scope has a ScopeStatus class, so this might need to be refactored to InstrumentStatus rather than having two different value objects that represent the same thing. However, this is being said without delving too deep yet into instrument status so perhaps there is a reason to have two implementations.

Summary: Technical: Make sure exceptions are handled consistently throughout the application
Creator: Seamus Johnson
Description:
We need to take the following steps to ensure that exceptions are handled in a consistent way throughout the application: # Server side: Those instances of us just throwing an exception and displaying it to the user absolutely need to be refactored to use DomainException, and ensure they are using a localizable resource string. # Client side: Do a find and replace on every instance of ".exceptionMessage" (17 files, 31 instances) and replace it with ".message" to conform to the error format for an expected 400 level error. Re-run the unit tests to make sure we didn't break stuff. # Use a directive to replace instances of: ng-class="{'has-error': ctrl.formController.name.$invalid }" (see: https://gist.github.com/jwcarroll/e0018b9d20ddf5c12e9f) # Client side: Create directive to replace instances of "
{{ctrl.error.exceptionMessage}}
"

Summary: Consistent Validation for Inline Editing in Kendo Grid
Creator: Rik Robinson
Description:
Inline grid validation in kendo grids is not working and is inconsistent. Some of this is because of the returned error data from the server. This will be addressed in separate story (link coming soon). 

Scope steps is the first place that we have used inline grid editing. See https://censis.atlassian.net/browse/CVN-720 for several visual defects that are currently raised. 

We do not want errors in a validation summary. Ideally, we'd like to not have the validation message showing above/below the input. Instead, it should be consistent with the approach shown in https://censis.atlassian.net/browse/CVN-480 for standard inputs (colored border). Note that we may also want to overlay an exclamation icon or something ON the input to allow color-blind users to find the invalid inputs). Once the validation is being shown as described IN the row, custom code can be removed that was keeping the validations from being cut off.

Summary: Ensure client is setting locale based on server locale
Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
From [Sprint Retro 7|https://censis.atlassian.net/wiki/display/CVN/Sprint+7+Retrospective]. 

The server will pull in the locale of the currently executing process, but the client (browser) needs to be informed of that in order to appropriately set the locale for DateTime formatting and localized text. 

The following need to be informed of the locale on the client side: 

* Angular (https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$locale) 
* Angular-Translate (http://angular-translate.github.io/docs/#/api/pascalprecht.translate.$translateProvider#methods_preferredlanguage) 
* Kendo UI (http://docs.telerik.com/kendo-ui/framework/localization/overview) 

For both Angular and Kendo, the appropriate language resource files need to be include, which should be easy enough to do within the Razor template for the layout based on the current locale.

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a technician I want to view instrument data by scanning the Censimark. +Acceptance Criteria+ * A technician can see instrument details such as vendor name, catalog number, description, alias, serial number, owner, status, current container, uses before service, uses since last service, total uses, sterilization method, sterilized status, integrity testing, last integrity test date, purchase date, expiration date, warranty expiration date, and asset ID. * Clicking the Supplier Info links [shows me vendor information|^screenshot-4.png], such as vendor name, address, [etc|^vendorDetails.png]. * Clicking the Search link allows me to search for another instrument. * I can [print labels from this page|^instrumentLabelPrint.png]. * If our subscription includes OneSource then the link takes me to the relevant page. * If service is required then [that is indicated to me|^requiredServiceIsIndicated.png]. Use symbol rather than just a color. * I can [print this information|^itemInfoPrint.pdf]. * If the "Special Handling" field contains Carriage Return characters, those should be translated to HTML
tags. (item_mark 3000000035 in DB HL_1219 is an example of this) * If the Product's uses before repair is greater than the instrument's uses since last repair, then the instrument is overdue for repair and this should be visually indicated on the "Uses Since Last Service" field. (see "Overdue Query" below to get records which match this condition) * If the product has been deleted, it should be visually indicated to the user. \\ \\ {panel:title=(i) Notes} * ItemInfo.asp * ClientOption 281 = OneSource * [Special scope stuff|^scopeMedia.png] going on. * I think that there's some dead code, such as [strVendorContact, strVendorUrl, etc|^vendorDetails.png] in this page. * Clicking the History link shows me the same details as on the ['search for instruments by description'|https://censis.atlassian.net/browse/CVN-52] page. * Printing a label posts the contents of the frmLabelPrint form to InstBarcodePrint.asp, which includes WriteBarcode128B.asp. {panel} {panel:title=Overdue query} {code:sql} SELECT * FROM HL_Item i INNER JOIN HL_VendorProduct p on p.product_id = i.product_id WHERE i.uses_since_last_repair > p.hl_uses_before_repair AND p.hl_uses_before_repair > 0 {code} {panel}

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a manager I want to edit product details so that instrument attributes are accurate. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* When adding a new product to the local instrument catalog, I can choose whether it will be a specific or generic instrument. Specific instruments refer to instruments that have been assigned a specific catalog number, supplier, and instrument name. Generic instruments refer to instruments that have been entered with only an instrument name. 
* If I know the catalog number, as I type it a list of matching catalog numbers already in my product catalog appears. 
* If I select a catalog number then the description and supplier fields will be populated. 
* If I'm editing a product then [the catalog number can't be changed|^theLimitsToEditingAnExistingProduct.png]. 
* I can the enter or update the Alias, which can be up to 200 characters in length. 
* I can enter a value for Estimated Cost between -922,337,203,685,477.5808 to 922,337,203,685,477.5807. 
* I can enter or update the Standard Time, which can be a number ranging from -2^15 (-32,768) to 2^15-1 (32,767), even though a decimal is present in the input field. 320.1 is saved as 3201. 
* I may enter Service Requirements by Number of Uses OR by a time limit. If I enter a number for time limit, I must also select a time Period (Days, Weeks, Months, Quarters, Years). 
* I may enter a number (-2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647) of uses after which the Product will be considered Expired. 
* I may enter a Warranty, including a time Period (Months, Years), expressed as a number -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647. 
* I can select a Sterilization Method from a dropdown list (maintained by Users at Admin>Sterilization Methods). 
* I may select as many as three Alternate Sterilization Methods. 
* I can specify that an Integrity Test is required. 
* I can specify Special Handling instructions up to 300 characters in length. 
* I can specify whether the Product is to appear on the Peel Pack page. 
* I can enter a Reference number up to 32 characters in length. 
* I can mark a product as deleted. 
* From this page I can navigate to a page where I can [manage Substitutions|^productSubs.png]. 
* From this page I can [navigate to a page where I can add or update images|^productImage.png]. 
* From this page I can [navigate to a page where I can add or update media|^productMedia.png]. 
* If I have a OneSource subscription then I can view instructions for use (IFU). 

\\ 
\\ 
{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
* Not all data can be edited. There's a [concept in this page called 'model locking'|^modelLocked.png]. 
{panel}

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a user with the '[change status of a marked instrument|^requiredPermission.png]' permission I can mark an instrument as loaned, repaired, replaced or disposed so that inventory status is accurate. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* I can [change status|^statusChoices.png] to Active, Repair Request, Replace Request, Loan Request, or Disposal Request. 
* I can select a reason for maintenance. 'Other' will always be present, and will be the first option, followed by the other reasons sorted in alphabetical order. 
* If Reason is Other I can enter an explanation of up to 30 characters in length. 

{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
* This function is used to mark an instrument that needs to be loaned, repaired, replaced or disposed. A damaged or worn instrument may be marked for replacement, repair, or maintenance (such as sharpening). The marked instrument must be approved by a CS Manager before any action can be taken. 
* Reference page: ItemStatusChange.asp 
* [MaintenanceReason|^MaintenanceReasonList.png] table contains the reasons for maintenance. 
{code:sql} 
Select maintenance_id, maintenance from MaintenanceReason order by maintenance 
{code} 
* Note that there is some [status change logic involving current status|^statusTransitionLogic.png]. 
* See Censitrac Online User Manual topic 'Marking an Instrument for Maintenance' for more information. ( \\censisServer02\censis\Product Development\Censitrac vNext\docs ) 
{panel}

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a manager I want to keep a record of instrumentation that is being sent out for maintenance or repair. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* I can select or scan items. 
* List of selectable items is sorted by the item mark. 
* I can see the item's status, its catalog number, last modified date, requestor's identity, estimated cost (if available), and request reason. 
* If catalog number is present then I will see vendor and catalog number. 
* I can choose whether to approve or deny or update (AKA 'No Change') maintenance requests. 
* If I enter a date then it must be valid. 
* I can specify a pickup location by entering a location or selecting from a [typeahead list|^locationList.png]. 
* I can enter an estimated return date. 
* I can enter a pickup date, which defaults to today's date. 
* I can select the vendor to whom the instruments were sent. 
* I can enter or update repair details. 
* I can enter a purchase order number. 
* I can enter the return date. 
* I can enter or update the repair reason. 
* I can enter the estimated cost impact. 
* I can assign a new serial number. 

\\ 
\\ 
{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
* Reference page: Marked.asp 
* Access seems to be [controlled by a BBB|^maintenanceAccess.png]. 
* Equipment marks start with 'Q'. 
* SQL for dropdown list: 
{code:sql} 
select item_mark,item_id,vendor_product_name 
from hl_item 
inner join hl_itemstatus on hl_itemstatus.item_status_id=hl_item.item_status_id 
inner join product_view p on p.product_id=hl_item.product_id 
where item_status like '%Request%' or item_status like '%Returned%' 

union 

select 'Q' + convert(varchar,equipment_id) as item_mark,equipment_id as item_id,rtrim(equipment_name) + ' ' + t.eqtype_name as vendor_product_name 
from hl_equipment 
inner join hl_eqtype t on t.eqtype_id=hl_equipment.eqtype_id 
inner join HL_EquipmentStatus on HL_EquipmentStatus.equipment_status_id=hl_equipment.equipment_status_id 
inner join hl_vendorequipment on hl_vendorequipment.eqproduct_id=hl_equipment.eqproduct_id 
where equipment_status like '%Request%' or equipment_status like '%Returned%' 
order by item_mark 
{code} 
* Not certain whether this works yet: 
{code} 
function window_onload() { 
scanner_setInterval(5000); 
setMonitor(true); 

SetActivityType(thisForm.ActionType.value) 

if( msg.value!='') AlertUser(msg.value) 

g_LocationPopup = new _jquery_popup_text(thisForm.txtLocation,'MarkedLookup.asp','SearchLocations') 
g_LocationPopup.onclickfn = popupListCallback; 
} 
{code} 

{panel}

Summary: Search For Instrument History By Description
Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a technician I want to view instrument history by searching for its product description. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* Results are listed alphabetically by description. 
* Results at the root level are limited to 500 and if there are more a message will be displayed asking the user to be more specific. 
* The top level of detail shows Vendor Product information including: supplier, catalog number, and description. 
* The next level of detail shows Instrument information including: updated timestamp, person responsible for the record, location, container that has the instrument, and status. 
* The third level of detail will [contain historical information|^descriptionSearchResults.png] about the Instrument including: updated timestamp, person responsible for the record, location, container that has the instrument, and status. 
* If a vendor product has an associated image then I can [view the image|^screenshot-4.png]. 
* If a vendor product does NOT have an associated image, the View Image capability is hidden. 
* I can [print the results|^instSearchResults.pdf] . 

\\ 
\\ 
{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
* There is some crazy permission stuff at work here. 'ItemInfo' and 'Scopes' are checked, but if you have only access to one of these then you can get to the page. 
{code:sql} 
SELECT access_type FROM Screen_Access_view sav join GL_Client c on c.client_id=1004 WHERE file_name = 'ItemInfo ' 
AND access_level_id = 103 and ((c.tier_template_id is not null) or (sav.tier_flags & c.tier_flags>0)) 
{code} 
* Apparently the individual permissions for this page, such as 'view history' don't apply; this is an all-or-nothing page [controlled by a BBB setting|^BBBAccessLevels.png]. At the database level if I don't have [the correct record in the ScreenAccess|^requiredDbRecord.png] table then the BBB is not displayed at all. 
* When ItemInfo.asp loads, access to ItemInfo.asp and Scopes.asp is checked by calling Security.asp's UserAccessByPage function. Creator: Dave Baskin
Description:
Censitrac has Scope entities that are already implemented and in use. However, the actual business model is that a Scope is just a special type of Instrument. Unfortunately, both Scopes and Instruments are stored in the same database table, "HL_Item". Scopes are Instruments where the "scope_type_id" column is not null (which should link to the "HL_ScopeType" table, but evidently there are cases where the data is invalid and the link is not correct). 

There are some ways to map this entity model to the database, but after evaluating these solutions and further discussion, it seems like the best way moving forward would be to do the following: 

# Create an Instrument entity that holds all of the information from current Scope entity. 
# Map the Instrument entity, rather than the Scope entity, to the HL_Item table. 
# Modify Scope to be unmapped but derive from the Instrument entity. 
# Modify the queries that were previously on the Scope entities to use the Instrument entity instead (and also ensure that Scope queries are filtering just the scope items from the total list of all Instruments). 
# Where the Scope object is needed, create a mapping object from Instrument to Scope.

* How do I know whether multiple facilities are defined? 
{code:sql} 
select count(*) as [count] 
from hl_facility 
where (coalesce(facility_code,'')<>'' or default_flag='Y') and status='A' 
{code} 
{code:sql} 
SELECT facility_id, facility_name, default_flag 
FROM HL_facility where status='A' 
ORDER BY facility_name 
{code} 
* Sample SQL that retrieves case cart types related to facility 1001 and all that are currently scanned to a location within the specified facility, plus all that are not assigned to any facility. 
{code:sql} 
select distinct set_id, set_status_id, set_name 
from hl_set s left outer join 
(select distinct a.parent_set_id, l.facility_id 
from HL_Set a inner join HL_Location l ON l.location_id = a.location_id 
where a.parent_set_id is not null and a.location_id is not null) af on af.parent_set_id=s.set_id 
where set_type='D' and set_hierarchy='S' and s.set_status_id <>117 and (s.facility_id = 1001 or s.facility_id is null or af.facility_id = 1001 ) 
order by set_name 
{code} 
* HL_Set.set_type = 'D' which means Definition. 
{panel}

{code:sql} 
SELECT sci.user_name checkin_user, sco.user_name checkout_user, c.loaner_case_id, c.loaner_proc_id, proc_name, status as case_status, case when status='A' then 'Active' else 'Closed' end as status_text, due_timestamp, case_ref, case_doc, rep_name, dest_name, checkin_timestamp, checkout_timestamp, notes, picked_up_by,

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* If RTLS interface is enabled and a subscription exists, then messages are created for rename of Case Cart Types. 
* If RTLS interface is enabled and a subscription exists, then messages are created for additions of new Case Carts. 
* If RTLS interface is enabled and a subscription exists, then messages are created for deletions of new Case Carts. 
* If RTLS interface is enabled and a subscription exists, then messages are created when a Case Cart is undeleted. 


+Rename Case Cart Type+ 
{code:none} 
if err<>0 then 
RenameCart= "Error: " & err.description 
else 
if sRtlsOption="S" then createRtlsList "TrayList", set_id 
if sRtlsOption="Y" then 
if HasMessageSubscription(107)="Y" then CreateInventoryUpdateEventMessage "", "set", "update", set_id, "", "", "" 
end if 
RenameCart="ok" 
end if 
{code} 


+Add Case Cart+ 
{code:none} 
if msg="" then 
AddActualSet=new_set_id 
'new tray list sent to output for rtls system 
if sRtlsOption="S" then createRtlsList "TrayList", new_set_id 
if sRtlsOption="Y" then 
if HasMessageSubscription(107)="Y" then CreateInventoryUpdateEventMessage new_set_id, "set", "add", "", "", "", "" 
end if 
else 
AddActualSet=msg 
end if 
{code} 


+Delete Case Cart+ 
{code:none} 

if err<>0 then 
DeleteActual="Error: " & err.description 
Else 
DeleteActual=r 'number of rows affected 
'new tray list sent to output for rtls system 
if sRtlsOption="S" then createRtlsList "TrayList", set_id 
if sRtlsOption="Y" then 
if HasMessageSubscription(107)="Y" then CreateInventoryUpdateEventMessage set_id, "set", "delete", "", "", "", "" 
end if 
End IF 

{code} 

+Undelete Case Cart+ 
{code:none} 
if err<>0 then 
UnDeleteActual="Error: " & err.description 
Else 
UnDeleteActual=set_status 'status text 
'new tray list sent to output for rtls system 
if sRtlsOption="S" then createRtlsList "TrayList", set_id 
if bCreateHL7 then CreateHL7Output set_id, false, true 
if sRtlsOption="Y" then 
if HasMessageSubscription(107)="Y" then CreateInventoryUpdateEventMessage set_id, "set", "undelete", "", "", "", "" 
end if 
End IF 
{code} 
{code:sql} 
exec sp_executesql N'select * from MQ_Subscriptions m 
where m.event_type_id=@P1',N'@P1 varchar(8000)','107' 
{code}

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a manager I want to create new container types so that inventory can be properly reprocessed. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* I must enter a unique container type name that is no more than 80 characters in length. 
* I must select a Service. 
* I must select a Sterilization Method from a list. 
* I can optionally choose up to three alternate Sterilization Methods from a list. 
* I can choose a Storage Location from a list of Locations that have Location Type = Storage. 
* I can choose an Assembly Location from a list of Locations that have Location Type = Assembly. 
* I may choose one of two Service Requirement parameters. Either a Number of Uses or a Number of Time Periods. If I choose Number of Uses, then I must enter a number indicating how many uses. If I select Number of Time Periods, then I must enter how many and select from a list the appropriate Time Period (Days, Weeks, Months, Qtrs, Years). 
* I may enter a Physician name to be associated with the container type with a maximum character length of 80. 
* I may enter a Standard Assembly Time of type numeric(6,2). 
* I may enter a Processing Cost in 'money' format with a maximum length of 15. 
* I may enter a Reference Number up to 30 characters in size. 
* I may enter a Weight of size decimal(9,6) size. 
* I may enter Decontam Instructions, up to 2,147,483,647 characters. 
* I may enter Assembly Instructions, up to 2,147,483,647 characters. 
* I may enter Sterilization Instructions, up to 2,147,483,647 characters. 
* I may enter Count Sheet Comments, up to 2,147,483,647 characters. 
* I may indicate that a Biological Indicator is required for Sterilization of the container type. 
* I may indicate that a Class 6 Test is required for Sterilization of the container type. 
* I may indicate that the container type is to be processed via Assembly by Exception. 
* I may indicate that the container type will have [Automatic Actuals|https://censis.atlassian.net/browse/CVN-346]. 
* I may indicate that the container type will have Soft Wrap. 
* I may choose a Priority from a list (Normal, Always Hot, Always Stat). 
* Permission Containers: Add, Delete, Update Container Names required. 
\\ 
\\ 

{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
* ContainerNew.asp eventually calls 'createContainer' function in HL_PageObjects.asp, inserting data into the HL_Set table. 
* The table HL_SetEx makes its first appearance here, storing Count Sheet Comments AKA 'picklist_text' as well as decontamination, assembly, and sterilization instructions as SQL Server text data types. 
* Assembly by Exception is HL_SetEx.reverse_assy_flag, char(1). 
* Assembly by exception feature usage is captured in the 2 'Censitrac Assembly by Exception' spreadsheet attachments. 
* 'BI Required' is persisted in HL_Set.biotest_flag with a value of 'Y'. Otherwise it is 'N' unless 'Class 6 Required' is checked- then it is 6. 
* 'Class 6 Required' is represented by '6' in the HL_Set.biotest_flag field. Usage stats are shown in Class6RequiredUsage.xls attachment. 
* If both 'BI Required' and 'Class 6 Required' checked then the value of HL_Set.biotest_flag is 'B'. 
* Apparently 'Automatic Actuals' is represented by HL_Set.parent_set_id is NULL and HL_Set.disposable_flag is 'Y', representing enable Automatic Actuals and 'N' representing... manual actuals? 
* 'Soft Wrap' is captured in HL_SetEx.rigidity and is represented by an 'S'. It appears when this isn't set the value is 'H' presumable for 'Hard'. 
{panel} 
* See Scott's mock-up: https://censis.atlassian.net/wiki/display/CVN/Censistrac+vNext+Refresh+UI+Mock-ups?preview=/7700568/7700566/image2015-6-3%2014%3A57%3A11.png

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a user I can check in loaner trays in advanced mode so that my facility can use loaned instruments. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* I can optionally enter or select a case procedure name. 
* If this was a previously used case procedure name then a list of trays previously used for this procedure will be displayed. Items from this list [can be deselected|^previouslyUsedContainers.png]. Additional trays can still be added to this list. Changes to the procedure contents are saved and will show on future check-ins. 
* I can optionally enter or select a Case ID. 
* If my facility utilizes the OR Scheduling interface, then Case ID can be selected. This will automatically populate Case Date, Time, Case Location, and Physician from the schedule data. 
* [When "Make Loaner case fields optional" is not selected in Administration > Settings|https://censis.atlassian.net/browse/CVN-638] then I must enter or select a Case Date. 
* Case Date can't be in the past or more than 14 days from now. 
* I can optionally enter a Case Time. (If a time isn't specified then midnight is used as the time.) 
* See comment below regarding time shortcut data entry. 
* When "Make Loaner case fields optional" is not selected in Administration > Settings then I must enter a Case Location. 
* When "Make Loaner case fields optional" is not selected in Administration > Settings then I must enter a Physician. 
* I can optionally enter a Vendor Rep Name. 
* I can optionally enter Notes. 
* I must select from the "Loaner Name in Censitrac" list. 
* I can optionally enter a Vendor's Loaner Name if different from what my facility has entered as a loaner name. The name does not have to be unique. This name will be displayed on the barcode label rather than the value of 'Loaner Name in Censitrac'. 
* I can [print a summary of the case|^printLoanerAdvanced.pdf] which if there are images, shows them full page. 

\\ 
\\ 
{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
* Please review the [standard mode story|https://censis.atlassian.net/browse/CVN-569] as there is much shared logic between this story and that one. 
* Note that if multi-facility logic is in effect then facility settings trump shared settings. 
* Print case summary details from Help: 
To print a summary of the case, click on the Censitrac logo at the top left of the header, and select Print from the dropdown. To include pictures in the printout, make sure to click the blue plus (+) next to Pictures so they are visible. 
{panel}

Description:
As a manager I want to create and manage a list of instrument substitutions for a container. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* I can scan an instrument or search the local instrument catalog by vendor, catalog number, or instrument name. 
* I can search for specific or generic instruments. Specific instruments refer to instruments that have been assigned a specific catalog number, supplier, and instrument name. Generic instruments refer to instruments that have been entered with only an instrument name. 
* Selecting a vendor limits the data returned for catalog number and instrument name. 
* If a vendor is selected then [I can select or type catalog number or name|^selectCatNumOrNameWhenVendorSelected.png]. 
* I can [view product details|^viewProductDetails.png] from the search results. 
* I can [add instruments to my local catalog|^addProductFromSub.png]. 
* If I select a deleted product then I am alerted. 
* I can allow new instruments to be 'cross substitutions' meaning that each instrument can be substituted for the other in any circumstance. By default 'Allow' is enabled. 
* If cross substitutions are allowed then the substitution list for each product must be accessed to remove it from the list. 
* I can selectively [allow instruments to be substituted as a marked item|^allow.png]. 
* I can remove substitutions from the list. 
* I can [print this page|^ContainerSubs.pdf] . 

\\ 
\\ 
{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
Substitutions.asp 
{panel}

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a manager I can enter instrument substitute information that can be used system-wide. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* I can scan an instrument into the substitution list. 
* I can search for specific instruments, which are instruments that have been assigned a specific catalog number, supplier, and instrument name 
* I can [search for generic instruments|^genericSearch.png], which are instruments that have been entered with only an instrument name. 
* I can [filter my search by vendor|^searchingForInstrumentByVendor.png] so that only relevant catalog numbers or names are displayed as options. 
* I can indicate on an instrument by instrument basis that each instrument can be substituted for the other in any circumstance ("Cross Substitution"). 
* I can [specify that every new substitution is a cross substitution|^allSubsAreCross.png]. 
* I can remove substitution rules. 
* I can view product details for the item that I am considering substituting. 
* I can add specific and [generic|^productAddedFromUniversalSubPage.png] products. 
* I can [print this page|^UniversalSub.pdf] .

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a manager I want to view the list of substitutions so that I know the substitutes for specific containers. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* List is grouped by alphabetical service name. 
* I can expand service name to see container definition and total number of substitutions for that container listed alphabetically by container name under the relevant service. 
* I can expand the container to view the substitutions for that container. 
* After container expansion I can see each instrument's vendor name, catalog number, description, placement and valid number of substitutions for that instrument for the container, sorted by placement. If an image is available for the instrument then I can optionally view it. 
* I can view the substitutions for an instrument by expanding the instrument row. 
* For each substitution I can specify a container and/ or universal rule. 
* If a universal rule is allowed then the substitution is valid for any container, not just the current parent container. 
* If a container rule is allowed then the universal rule is ignored. If a container rule is not allowed then the instrument can not be used as a substitute for this container. 
* I can add a new universal substitution rule or a container substitution rule by clicking the instrument row in the container definition. 
* I can filter decided substitutions so that I can view and approve substitutions made recently with the "Add Marked" feature during container assembly. 
* I can [print this page|^SubList.pdf] . 

\\ 
\\ 

{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
Initial list query: 
{code:sql} 
select s.set_id, p.procedure_name, s.set_name, sum(case when subv.substitute_product_id is null then 0 else 1 end) as subs 
from hl_set s 
inner join hl_procedure p on p.procedure_id=s.procedure_id 
left join hl_setitem si on si.set_id=s.set_id 
left join substitution_view subv on (subv.product_id=si.product_id and subv.parent_set_id=s.set_id) 
where s.set_type='D' and s.set_hierarchy='C' and s.set_status_id<>117 
group by s.set_id, p.procedure_name, s.set_name order by p.procedure_name, s.set_name 
{code} 

{panel}

Summary: Handle Reprints for Serialized Data Greater than 8000 Characters
Creator: Dave Baskin
Description:
In the database, the PicklistReprint table has a column, "print_data", that is used to store the serialized version of the Picklist reprint data. Since the column is defined as a VARCHAR(8000), then the size of the serialized data is limited to 8,000 characters. In the Classic application if the data was bigger than that, then the reprint data was just not stored. 

It was decided that in the interest of time, the VNext application should do the same thing rather than risking a modification that might break the Classic application functionality. 

This story is to do the work to allow for serializing reprint data greater than 8000 characters.

Creator: Steven Porter
Description:
As a manager I want to use automatic actuals so that I don't have to explicitly manage container instances. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* I won't see containers listed under the container type when automatic actuals are used. 
* I won't have the option to add an actual container but instead will have the option to [print an assembly label|^printAssemblyLabelMenu.png]. 
* Permission Containers: Print Labels required. 
* Because I am a manager [I can do everything there is to do on this page|^managerPermissions.png]. Just like when automatic actuals aren't used I can edit service names, container names, navigate to and edit container types and count sheets, etc. 

{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
* Select the option labeled "Automatic Actuals" if this container definition is for a set of marked instruments that will not be tracked at the actual instance level. Censitrac will automatically manage the creation and deletion of the actuals as trays are assembled and disassembled. All historical data will be consolidated and displayed throughout Censitrac under the container name without any reference to a sequence number. This option would normally be used for sets of marked instruments that do not have a permanent physical container. 
* Apparently 'Automatic Actuals' is represented by HL_Set.parent_set_id is NULL and HL_Set.disposable_flag is 'Y', representing enable Automatic Actuals and 'N' representing... manual actuals? 
* Container.asp's code further reinforces this by using a variable named 'fDisposable' to drive the 'automatic actual' logic. 
* Apparently the set_id for an automatic actual will be the letter 'D' with the container definition / type's set_id. Example: D1103 for a container type with set_id of 1103. 
* Here is a demonstration of Automatic Actuals: 
{noformat} 
\\censisServer02\censis\Product Development\Censitrac vNext\recordings\AutoActualsTechnicalWalkthrough.mp4 
{noformat} 

{panel}

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* I can select a reprocessor to use. 
* If no machines are available then [I am informed of this sad fact|^noMachinesAvailable.png]. 
* Scan a location TK 

\\ 
\\ 
{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
* Given the SQL below, the correct scanned value sent to Censitrac would be L1058 or L1059. 
{code:sql} 
select l.location_id, l.location, l.sterilization_method_id 
from hl_location l 
left join HL_SterilizationMethod sm on sm.sterilization_method_id=l.sterilization_method_id 
left join hl_sterilizercycle sc on sc.ster_cycle_id=sm.ster_cycle_id 
left join censis_beta_v2_global..SterilizerCycleType sct on sct.cycle_type=coalesce(sc.cycle_type,sm.ster_cycle_id) 
where l.status='A' 
and coalesce(sct.sterilant_type,sm.sterilant_type) in (11, 23, 24, 25, 28, 31, 35, 36) 
and coalesce(l.facility_id,0)=1001 
order by l.location 
{code} 

{panel}

Creator: Bryant Brabson
Description:
As a user I want to use the standard loaner search so that I can find loaner trays. 

+Acceptance Criteria+ 
* I can search without specifying any criteria. This only shows active loaners. 
* I can search using some or all of the criteria. This shows active and closed. 
* I can search by specifying Case Procedure Name. 
* I can search by specifying or selecting Case ID. 
* I can search by specifying or selecting Case Date. 
* I can search by specifying Case Time. 
* I can search by specifying Case Location. 
* I can search by specifying Physician. 
* I can search by specifying Vendor Rep Name. 
* I can search by specifying any words contained in the Notes field. 
* Text fields (including case id) return partial matches, e.g. entering case id 10 will return case 2010. 
* Search results are ordered by Case Date (due_timestamp) if present otherwise checkin_timestamp, then Case Location (dest_name), then Physician (case_doc). 
* If search results are found then I can see Case, Case Date, Case Location, Physician, Check In date and time, Vendor Rep, Status, Check In By (the user who checked the trays in), Check Out By if present, and Loaner Quantity. 
* I can select a result row and select whether to check out or update the case. (See [CVN-916|https://censis.atlassian.net/browse/CVN-916]) 
* Retain search criteria in case I should choose to modify my search.

Description:
As a Technician, I need to be able to enter Indicator Results to ensure accuracy of sterilization data. 

Permissions that affect this page: Load Results: Remove indicator images. Access to update Load Results can be limited by the Competency Module. See Load Results Competency for more details. 

TK If a load indicator is in an incubator (see Load Indicators page), should we block updating that indicator from this page? 

Access to update Indicator Results can be limited by the Competency Module. See Indicator Results Competency for more details. 

I can see a list of all the indicators expected to be included in the load.  The indicators required would have been determined by the Cycle settings, and or a BI requirement for one or more of the contents. 

I can select a Positive or Negative Result for all Indicators that should have been in the load, or NA if the indicator was not actually included. The expected result will be the leftmost column under Result. A BI should have a Negative result if sterilization was achieved, but a BI Control should have a Positive Result (because a Control is NOT run thru Sterilization, but gets incubated to ensure the validity of the BI Lot). 

The Product will be pre-filled base on Group Settings. I can overwrite or enter a Product. 

I can enter a Lot Number. 

If results are already entered, they will be displayed, as well as the Date and User who entered them. 

If I have appropriate permissions, I can Clear any previously entered results. 

I can enter notes up to TK characters. 

I can select Scan Images to navigate to scan images of the indicators.

{panel:title=(i) Notes} 
SQL to reveal containers with messages. 

{code:sql} 
SELECT pr.procedure_name 
,st.set_name 
,msg.* 
,st.* 
FROM [dbo].[HL_SetMessage] sm 
join HL_Message msg on msg.message_id = sm.message_id 
inner join container_view st on st.set_id = sm.set_id 
inner join HL_Procedure pr on pr.procedure_id = st.procedure_id 
order by posted_date desc

Creator: Cathy Sanford
Description:
As a Supervisor I need to know that a Technician has a valid Competency record in order to update Indicator Results. 

Permissions affecting this story: 
Admin>Competency: May observe training 

*Acceptance Testing* 

* If a Competency record has been created that controls Indicator Results access, and the Competency record controls access to the Sterilizer of the load, then there must be a valid Training Record in place for the User who is logged in. 
* If a Competency record exists and the Employee does NOT have a valid Training record, the User should receive a Stop message. This event should be recorded for reporting purposes. 
* As a Supervisor with Competency observe permissions, I should be able to scan my Censitrac badge to invoke a Training Session which lasts only until results are recorded one time. 
* Once the Training Session has been confirmed, the User can continue recording the Indicator Results. 
* After the Results are recorded, as a Supervisor I must again scan my badge, and I should receive a message showing any Competencies that affect this process, allowing me to choose the one for which Training has occurred, and create an In Process Observation Record. 
* If I do NOT scan my badge a second time, no training record will be recorded. 
* If there is no Competency Record in place that affects Indicator Results for this Asset, then the employee may proceed without interruption.

Creator: Cathy Sanford
Description:
As a Technician I need to be able to update Sterilizier Results as long as I have a valid Competency record. 

*Acceptance Testing* 

* If a Competency record has been created that controls Load Results access, and the Competency record controls access to the Sterilizer of the load, And I have a valid training record in place, then I should be able to update Load Results. 
* If a Competency record exists and I do NOT have a valid Training record, I should receive a Stop message. This event should be recorded for reporting purposes.

Creator: Cathy Sanford
Description:
As a Technician I need to be able to update Load Details in order to record sterilization data. 

Permissions that affect this page: Load Results: Issue a recall for the contents of a load. Access to update Load Results can be limited by the Competency Module. See Load Results Competency for more details. 

The specific fields displayed on this page are controlled by the configuration set up on the Load Details for the group the machine belongs to.  (See Modifying Sterilizer Group Settings for more information). Available fields are: Location, Load Number, Load Scanned, Added, Load Result, Alarm, Cycle, Sterilant Batch, Case Reference, Reason, Temperature, Sterilization Time, Dry Time, Saved, Notes. 

Load Number: 
* If I come directly into this page, I can search for a Load Number, or enter one directly. 
* If I scan a Sterilizer Location, the search results will be limited to that Sterilizer. 
* If multiple Facilities exist, the search results will be limited to Locations within that Facility. 
* If the load number is not found after scanning a location and searching for an exact load number, the search function will then search for that load number in all locations for the facility that was selected during the user's login process. 
* In order to search for load numbers that begin with the same pattern, enter the criteria in the "load Number" box.  By entering the criteria followed by an asterisk, the search results are limited to load numbers that begin with the same pattern.  For example, in order to display a list of load numbers beginning with "020806", enter "020806*" in the "load Number" field, and then press or click the "Search" button.   
* If I navigated into this page from another, the Load Number will be prefilled. 
* If the Load number was a user entered one, I can update it, if it was automatically assigned by Censitrac, it cannot be changed. See Modifying Sterilizer Group Settings for more information. 
* If I scan any label that is not a Location, I will get a Stop message. 
* If I scan a Location Label that is not a Sterilizer, I will get a Stop message. 

I can view the Location, Load Number, Load Scanned Timestamp, Added by User, Load Added Timestamp (TK why different?) Last Saved Timestamp, Last Saved User. 

If the Sterlizer is interfaced, and the tape has been received (and matched TK), then the following information will be pulled from the tape: 
Alarm, Cycle (Type), Temperature, Sterilization Time, Dry Time, (Cycle Details). 

If an active Competency exists for this Sterilizer AND I have an Approved and Current Competency record, then I can update the Load Result by selecting the appropriate button. If I do NOT have a valid Competency record, I will receive a message, and a Supervisor may do a temporary override for training purposes. See Load Results Competency for more information. 

I can update the Alarm by selecting from a list. 
I can update the Cycle by selecting from a list. Cycles to appear in the list can be controlled by the Group Cycles settings page. (Reference to Modifying Sterilizer Group Settings for more info.) 
I can update the Sterilant Batch. 
I can update the Case Reference. 
I can update the Reason by selecting from a list. 
I can update the Temperature. 
I can update the Sterilization Time. 
I can update the Dry Time. 
TK-Does this add to Cycle List if not already there? 
I can enter notes about the load as needed up to TK characters. 

Tape 
If the Sterilizer is interfaced to Censitrac, and a Tape has been associated with this load, I can view the electronic Tape by selecting the Tape button. 
If the Sterilizer is interfaced to Censitrac, and no Tape has been associated yet, and Tape Matching is set for this Location, the Tape button will be disabled, and the Find Tape button will be enabled. I can select Find Tape, and a list of unmatched tapes will be shown. I can select a Tape from that list to be associated with this load. 
TK scan tape 

I can navigate to Contents list. 
I can navigate to Indicators page. 
I can navigate to (Comprehensive) Load report. 

I can Issue a Recall.

Creator: Cathy Sanford
Description:
As a Technician, I need to view all indicators for washer loads in order to ensure all have been properly recorded. 

If only Washers are showing on the list, the display will show: 

* Load 
* Start Timestamp 
* Cycle 
* Washer 
* Sonic 
* Water 
* Temp 

Green highlight means the result was recorded as passed.  If multiples of this test are used, all must be recorded as passed for a green highlight to display. Yellow highlight will display if there was a prompt to run this test in that load and the result has not yet been recorded.  If multiples of this test are used, a yellow highlight will display until all are results are recorded. Red highlight will display when the result was recorded as failed. If multiples of this test are used, a red highlight will display if a fail is recorded for any of the results. 

TK There has been discussion that the color codes are not ADA compliant. So we need to establish a standard...

Creator: Cathy Sanford
Description:
As a Technician I need to view a list of Loads and their Indicator Results to verify all have been correctly documented. 

If Sterilizers and Washers, or only Sterilizer loads are selected, Loads will be listed with the following data: 

* Load number 
* Start Timestamp 
* Cycle 
* Bowie-Dick - Yes if Load was a Bowie-Dick run, otherwise blank. 
* BI Prompt - Yes if a BI Prompt was given when Load sent, otherwise blank. 
* BI results - Yes if BI results have been recorded, otherwise blank. 
* BI growth results - Yes if BI growth results have been recorded, otherwise blank. 
* BI Control results - Yes if BI Control results have been recorded, otherwise blank. 
* Class 6 prompt - Yes if Class 6 Prompt was given when Load sent, otherwise blank. 
* Class 6 results - Yes if Class 6 results have been recorded, otherwise blank. 
* CI results - Yes if CI results have been recorded, otherwise blank. 

Note: This will be reworked for VA, but no completion date has been set. The display will change considerably when that work is completed. I can't find the JIRA issue but it must be there because it would have been pulled from the case log... VA Phase 2 or 3 originally...

We have not been good about determining what a button should say, how many there should be, or what functionality should be. 

I propose: 
* Save-should save data and close dialog box 
* Cancel-should clear data and close dialog box

* I can enter a Catalog Reference Number.

Summary: Barcode Scan module should send standard messages for unrecognized labels
Creator: Cathy Sanford
Description:
As a user, tester, debugger, any hat, really, I want to see a standard set of messages when I scan a label that is not recognized. Each page should tell me: 

a) the type of barcode label (if it is a recognized label) or that it is a type unknown to Censitrac 
b) what barcode label types are valid on this page 
c) if the label type is valid, but the item is not found, it should tell me the type of item (barcode) and whether or not the item is found in the database 

Barcode Label Types: 

Marked Instrument 
Pre-Marked Instrument 
Peel Pack 
Tray 
Loaner (same as Tray or different?) 
Case Cart 
Scope 
Equipment 
Case Reference 
Employee Badge 
Location 
Bin (same as Location or different?) 
Tasks
